---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Defensive Patent Pledge" description="Evoked's irrevocable commitment not to assert its governance verification patents against good-faith actors. Modeled on Google, Tesla, and Red Hat precedents." hideFloatingChat={true}>
  <div class="hero">
    <p class="hero-above">Evoked</p>
    <h1>Defensive Patent Pledge</h1>
    <p class="tagline">Version 1.2 - March 28, 2026</p>
    <p class="version-note">Updated from v1.1 to reflect organization name change from Evoke Passion to Evoked (DBA effective March 16, 2026). No substantive terms changed.</p>
  </div>

  <section class="container pledge-body">

    <div class="pledge-section">
      <h2>The Pledge</h2>
      <p>
        Evoked irrevocably pledges not to assert its governance verification patents against any party
        acting in good faith, for the life of the patents, including any successors or assigns.
      </p>
      <p>
        This pledge is not a license. It is a binding commitment that Evoked will not initiate
        patent infringement claims against good-faith actors. The patents remain in force. The pledge
        governs how they are used.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="pledge-section">
      <h2>Who Is Protected</h2>
      <p>Evoked will not initiate a patent infringement lawsuit against any party that:</p>
      <p class="clause">
        <strong>(a)</strong> Implements agent governance validation - including governance property scanning,
        restraint specification assessment, or governance attestation - for open-source, non-commercial,
        academic, or research purposes;
      </p>
      <p class="clause">
        <strong>(b)</strong> Develops their own agent governance validation methodology, even if it validates
        similar governance properties, provided they do not copy the specific patented methods described in
        Evoked's patent claims;
      </p>
      <p class="clause">
        <strong>(c)</strong> Uses Evoked's published governance frameworks (Sovereignty Assessment Toolkit,
        Trust Architecture Blueprint, Agent Governance Starter Kit, Agent Restraint Specification Template,
        Agent Voice Architecture Guide, Agent Memory Architecture Guide) in any context;
      </p>
      <p class="clause">
        <strong>(d)</strong> Queries the Evoked Verification public API or embeds Evoked Verification
        badges.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="pledge-section">
      <h2>What This Pledge Does Not Protect</h2>
      <p>This pledge does not apply to any party that:</p>
      <p class="clause">
        <strong>(a)</strong> Patents a trivially modified version of Evoked's specific patented
        methodology and asserts it offensively against others - including against Evoked or any
        other entity building agent governance tools;
      </p>
      <p class="clause">
        <strong>(b)</strong> Uses Evoked's specific patented methods in a commercial product while
        simultaneously asserting patents against Evoked or its users;
      </p>
      <p class="clause">
        <strong>(c)</strong> Misrepresents agents or systems as Evoked-verified, Evoked-attested, or
        governance-validated by Evoked without holding a valid attestation;
      </p>
      <p class="clause">
        <strong>(d)</strong> Brings patent litigation against Evoked, its products, or its users for
        technology relating to AI agent governance, identity, or trust infrastructure.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="pledge-section">
      <h2>Good Faith</h2>
      <p>A party is acting in good faith for so long as that party and its affiliates have not:</p>
      <ol class="faith-list">
        <li>
          Asserted, helped others assert, or held a financial stake in any patent assertion against
          Evoked, its products, or its users;
        </li>
        <li>
          Challenged the validity of any Evoked patent except as a defense in litigation
          initiated by Evoked;
        </li>
        <li>
          Misrepresented their governance validation status using Evoked's name, marks,
          or attestation tiers.
        </li>
      </ol>
      <p>
        If a party ceases the activity that caused them to lose good-faith status - including permanent
        dismissal, withdrawal, or settlement of patent litigation - good-faith status is restored.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="pledge-section">
      <h2>Irrevocability and Transfer</h2>
      <p>
        This pledge is <strong>irrevocable</strong>. It binds Evoked and all successors, assigns,
        and transferees of the pledged patents. This pledge survives any change in legal form, structure,
        or organizational status of Evoked, including but not limited to incorporation, conversion,
        merger, or dissolution.
      </p>
      <p>
        If Evoked transfers, sells, or assigns any pledged patent, the transfer is subject to this
        pledge. The acquiring party inherits the pledge obligations. A transfer that attempts to circumvent
        this pledge is a breach of the transfer agreement.
      </p>
      <p>
        This pledge remains in force for the full life of each pledged patent, including any extensions
        or continuations.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="pledge-section">
      <h2>What This Pledge Is and Is Not</h2>
      <div class="is-isnot">
        <div class="is-col">
          <h3>This pledge IS:</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>A binding, irrevocable commitment not to assert patents offensively against good-faith actors</li>
            <li>Effective for the life of the patents</li>
            <li>Transferable - binds successors and assigns</li>
            <li>Consistent with the Evoked Prime Directive: we evoke, we never extract</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="isnot-col">
          <h3>This pledge IS NOT:</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>A license (no rights are granted to practice the patented methods). However, good-faith actors described above may practice the patented methods without seeking authorization from Evoked.</li>
            <li>A waiver of patent claims (the patents remain enforceable against bad-faith actors)</li>
            <li>A covenant not to sue (it is a pledge - breach of good faith restores assertion rights)</li>
            <li>Authorization to represent affiliation with Evoked or Evoked Verification</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="pledge-section">
      <h2>Pledged Patents</h2>
      <div class="patent-table-wrap">
        <table class="patent-table">
          <thead>
            <tr>
              <th>Application</th>
              <th>Title</th>
              <th>Filing Date</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <td>64/004,087</td>
              <td>Method and System for Validating Artificial Intelligence Agent Governance Properties Through a Certificate Authority Architecture</td>
              <td>March 12, 2026</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
      <p class="table-note">This table will be updated as additional patents are filed.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="pledge-section">
      <h2>Why This Pledge Exists</h2>
      <p>
        We filed this patent to protect the governance property certification space - not to own it.
        The prior art is vacant. Someone will patent agent governance validation. We chose to be the
        ones who do it, so we can choose how it is used.
      </p>
      <p>This pledge ensures:</p>
      <ol class="why-list">
        <li>
          <strong>Open-source governance tools are never threatened.</strong> Anyone building agent
          governance validation for the commons is protected, permanently.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Innovation is not blocked.</strong> Other organizations can build their own governance
          validation methodologies. The patent protects our specific methods. The pledge ensures the
          space stays open.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Bad actors cannot weaponize the gap.</strong> Without a defensive patent, a company
          with extractive intent could patent trivially modified versions of governance validation and
          use them offensively. This patent, combined with this pledge, closes that vector.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>The commons and the steward are both protected.</strong> The patent sustains Evoke
          Passion's ability to do this work. The pledge ensures the work serves the commons. Mutual
          aid means both directions.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>This is one governance tradition, not the only one.</strong> Our five properties
          emerge from Western liberal governance - individual rights, documented consent, structural
          accountability. Other traditions define governance differently. We built Evoked Verification from
          one tradition. We built the system to be extended, not to be the last word. No governance
          tradition should have to translate itself into ours to be recognized as governance.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Standards can become gates.</strong> This pledge governs how <em>we</em> use the patent.
          It does not govern how others adopt it. If this model becomes a procurement requirement, it could
          exclude agent systems whose governance looks different from ours - not because they lack governance,
          but because theirs was built from a different tradition. We name this risk so that adoption includes
          structural openness as a design requirement, not an afterthought.
        </li>
      </ol>
    </div>

    <div class="pledge-section contact-section">
      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>
        Questions about this pledge, licensing inquiries, or governance validation partnership:
      </p>
      <p class="contact-info">
        <strong>Erin Stanley</strong><br />
        Founder, Evoked<br />
        <a href="mailto:passionevoked@icloud.com">passionevoked@icloud.com</a> |
        <a href="/">evoked.dev</a>
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="pledge-closing">
      <p>"We evoke - we never extract."</p>
    </div>

  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .hero-above {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.15em;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-xs);
  }

  .version-note {
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    font-style: italic;
    margin-top: var(--space-xs);
  }

  .pledge-body {
    max-width: 720px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding-bottom: var(--space-xl);
  }

  .pledge-section {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-xl);
    padding-bottom: var(--space-lg);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-subtle);
  }

  .pledge-section:last-of-type {
    border-bottom: none;
  }

  .pledge-section h2 {
    font-size: 1.3rem;
    color: var(--text-primary);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
  }

  .pledge-section p {
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.8;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
  }

  .clause {
    padding-left: var(--space-md);
    border-left: 2px solid var(--border-accent);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
  }

  .faith-list,
  .why-list {
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.8;
    padding-left: var(--space-lg);
  }

  .faith-list li,
  .why-list li {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
  }

  .why-list li strong {
    color: var(--text-primary);
  }

  .is-isnot {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: var(--space-lg);
    margin-top: var(--space-md);
  }

  .is-isnot h3 {
    font-size: 1rem;
    color: var(--text-primary);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
  }

  .is-isnot ul {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
  }

  .is-isnot li {
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.7;
    padding-left: var(--space-md);
    position: relative;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
  }

  .is-col li::before {
    content: "\2713";
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: var(--accent-warm);
  }

  .isnot-col li::before {
    content: "\2717";
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: var(--text-muted);
  }

  .patent-table-wrap {
    overflow-x: auto;
    margin: var(--space-md) 0;
  }

  .patent-table {
    width: 100%;
    border-collapse: collapse;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
  }

  .patent-table th {
    text-align: left;
    padding: var(--space-sm) var(--space-md);
    border-bottom: 2px solid var(--border-accent);
    color: var(--text-primary);
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .patent-table td {
    padding: var(--space-sm) var(--space-md);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-subtle);
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  .table-note {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    font-style: italic;
  }

  .contact-info {
    color: var(--text-primary);
  }

  .contact-info a {
    color: var(--accent-warm);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 2px;
  }

  .contact-info a:hover {
    color: var(--accent-glow);
  }

  .pledge-closing {
    text-align: center;
    margin-top: var(--space-xl);
    padding-top: var(--space-lg);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border-accent);
  }

  .pledge-closing p {
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    font-size: 1.1rem;
  }

  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .is-isnot {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }
</style>
